Blurb::
Give the model block an identifying name, in case of multiple model blocks
Description::
The model independent controls include a model identifier string,
pointers to variables and responses specifications, and a model type
specification.  The model identifier string is supplied with \c
id_model and is used to provide a unique identifier string for use
within method specifications (refer to any of the keywords: \c model_pointer in
under one of the methods in the \ref method block, for example: 
\ref method-list_parameter_study-model_pointer)

